## Twitter Timeline

Definition:  Twitter is one of the most popular social networks used today
but it began as another micro-blogging platform created by programmers who worked
at the podcasting company Odeo Inc. in San Francisco, California.
The founders are Jack Dorsey (@Jack), Evan Williams (@Ev) and Biz Stone (@Biz)

How it [works](https://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/digital-culture/the-history-of-twitter-140-characters-at-a-time/article573416/)

Twitter as a [news source](https://abcnews.go.com/Technology/story?id=7979891&page=1)
- first coverage & people starting to see it as social media that can be purposeful/powerful

##### March 21, 2006 - 2:50 PM
- CEO Jack Dorsay sent first tweet "just setting up my twttr"
- The name Twitter came from @Noah Glass & the Oxford English:
"a short inconsequential burst of information, chirps from birds." ( possibly also inspired by Flickr)
- other names they considered:  FriendStalker and Dodgeball


##### Aug 23, 2007 - 1:25 PM
- the hashtag is created "how do you feel about using # (pound) for groups. As in #barcamp [msg]?" - Chris Messina ()

##### [June 11, 2015](https://www.wired.com/2015/06/twitter-ceo-dick-costolo-jack-dorsey-developing/)
- Dick Costolo is stepping down, while Twitter cofounder Jack Dorsey
has been appointed interim CEO effective at the beginning of July. Costolo
will continue to serve on Twitterâ€™s board.


#####  [March 21, 2016](https://www.wired.com/2016/03/10th-birthday-short-history-twitter-tweets/)
- Twitter turns 10 years old
- earning more than $500 million a quarter
- more than 300 million users
- used to spread news and live updates



